.TH LOCALFIRST-DISPATCH 8 "2026" "dsmr-localfirst" "DSMR mail stack"
.SH NAME
localfirst-dispatch \- delivery-time dispatcher for hybrid system/vpopmail domains
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B | /var/qmail/bin/localfirst-dispatch
.RI [ HOST ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B localfirst-dispatch
replaces a hybrid vpopmail domain's catch-all
.I .qmail-default
(normally
.RB \(oq "| /home/vpopmail/bin/vdelivermail '' delete" \(cq).
For the recipient local-part (qmail's
.B $DEFAULT
environment variable, falling back to
.BR $EXT ),
if it is a mail-eligible system identity (see
.BR system-identity (8))
the message is re-injected to
.IR LOCALPART @ HOST
via qmail's
.BR forward ,
so qmail-send delivers it to the system account with correct ownership.
Otherwise the original vpopmail catch-all
.RB ( "vdelivermail '' delete" )
is executed unchanged.
.PP
.I HOST
is the locals host domain to re-inject to. It is taken from the first argument;
if omitted, from
.IR /var/qmail/control/me .
It must differ from the vpopmail virtual domain so re-injection does not loop.
.SH NOTES
This program runs as the vpopmail user and deliberately does not touch any
recipient's
.IR ~/Maildir :
it cannot create a file owned by the target user. A recipient's Maildir is
created from
.I /etc/skel
at account creation; a delivery-time fallback (running as the target user)
creates it if absent.
.SH WIRING
.nf
.I .qmail-default :
| /var/qmail/bin/localfirst-dispatch b612.asteroid.radio
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR localfirst-rcptcheck (8),
.BR system-identity (8),
.BR forward (1)
